  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The second equation is three times the first, so they represent the same line. Solving 6x + 11y = 5 for y: y = (5 - 6x)/11. For x = r, the point is (r, (5 - 6r)/11). The other choices reflect incorrect rearrangements.</p>",
